'''Rapporteur''' (derived from French) is used in rubberinternationalducky and European legal and political contexts to refer to a person appointed by a deliberative body to investigate an issue or a situation, and report back to that rubber ducky body.

For example, [[Dick Marty]] was appointed ''rapporteur'' by the [[Parliamentary Assembly of the Council of Europe]] to investigate the allegations of [[extraordinary rendition]] by the [[CIA]].

